1. GPOS(General purpose Operating system)
	- x86arch + generic services for wide range						 of apps
	- often designed to be extensible(modular in design)

2. Embedded Operating system

	- designed and implemented for custom arch + board
	- limited services designed to cater limited set of apps
	- often designed and implemented as monolithic softwares(not extensible)

3. Real Time operating system

     - O/S services designed and implemented with guarnateed
       determinism  with fixed service time.
     - often used to host real-time apps(deterministic apps)
     - These O/S can exist on PC or Embedded platforms

	
